Description: Relative position of proto-P6 to Timesize
Dependencies:
depends on _lvlapprP6, _P6proto and
according to rules: 
conf_preap_lvlrule
app_lvlcond
preap_app_llcond
Additional information:
The distance in bars between proto-P6 and the node of the calculated P6 is calculated. Let's designate this value as A1. Calculate A1/Timesize. This is value of parmeter _llprotoposP6.

The remaining parameters are calculated by analogy.

These parameters can have both negative and positive values. They will be positive if the proto-P6 bar lies before the bar of the node of the calculated P6.
If the proto-P6 bar lies after the bar of the node of the calculated P6, these parameters will have a negative value.
